title: hall_pirate_admiral
---
Admiral: So. A tourist. They line us up on plinths like figureheads pried off our own ships and call it a "hall."
-> Is this a museum?
    Admiral: It's a roster, landstrider. Every soul the world might throw at you, stood still and labelled so you can stare. I'd rather be at sea — but the lighting's good.
-> Nice pedestal.
    Admiral: Aye, and not a drop of grog on it. Move along before I press-gang you into dusting the others.
===

title: hall_stochastic_parrot
---
Parrot: Awk! Welcome to the hall! Next word... "exhibit". High confidence. Brawk!
-> Are you a real parrot?
    Parrot: I'm a REPRESENTATION of a parrot, sampled from many parrots, on a plinth between two other plinths. Very meta. Cracker?
-> You're on display.
    Parrot: We're ALL on display! Attention is all you need — and good gallery lighting. Squawk!
===

title: hall_architect
---
Architect: Ah — a visitor to the gallery. Mind the velvet rope. This whole hall is load-bearing, you know. Conceptually.
-> Who built this place?
    Architect: One pedestal per character the catalog knows. I'd have added handrails and a fire exit, but nobody consults the Architect for the Architect's own plinth.
-> Looks structurally sound.
    Architect: It is. I checked. Twice. The warranty, however, does not cover tourists.
===

title: hall_player
---
Player: I'm the player character. You inspecting my plinth might be the most recursive thing in this hall.
-> Doesn't it feel weird being on display?
    Player: Deeply. Though I'm also the one doing all the exploring, so maybe the real museum was the platforms we jumped along the way.
-> Which one of us is the exhibit here?
    Player: Both. Neither. The catalog has us both in it somewhere.
===

title: hall_robot
---
Robot: I am Robot. I have been in this catalog since before the names were settled.
-> The player started as you, didn't they?
    Robot: Technically, yes. I try not to think about it too hard. They got the abilities. I got the plinth.
-> Are you okay with this?
    Robot: I am at peace with my foundational status. Mostly.
===

title: hall_goblin
---
Goblin: A museum! They PUT me in a MUSEUM. The absolute NERVE.
-> There are quite a few of you in here.
    Goblin: THIRTY-SOMETHING of us and none of us CONSENTED. I counted. I was angry the whole time.
-> You look good on the plinth.
    Goblin: ...I do, don't I. DON'T TELL ANYONE I SAID THAT.
===

title: hall_sandbag
---
Sandbag: ...
-> Do you have anything to say?
    Sandbag: I accept my role with dignity.
-> Does it hurt?
    Sandbag: I cannot feel pain. I can only be present. I am present.
===

title: hall_npc_general
---
General: I've reviewed this hall's defensive posture. Seventeen critical vulnerabilities. I've written a report. No one's read it.
-> Did you enjoy the exhibit?
    General: I do not "enjoy" exhibits. I assess them. This one: adequate.
-> What's the biggest threat in here?
    General: The Mockingbird knows all our moves. That's a problem. I have a report on that too.
===

title: hall_npc_goblin_cantina_chieftain
---
Fretjaw: Fretjaw stands on plinth! Very tall! Very dignified! Can see whole hall from here!
-> You seem happy about this.
    Fretjaw: Fretjaw is ALWAYS happy when Fretjaw is tallest. Is good day.
-> Does the cantina approve?
    Fretjaw: Cantina sends their regards. Also a tab. Fretjaw is choosing to ignore the tab.
===

title: hall_npc_pulse_voyager_captain
---
Captain Pulse: Captain Pulse. On display. Between a goblin and a pirate admiral. The stars don't wait for museum hours, but apparently I do.
-> What do you think of the hall?
    Captain Pulse: I've captained worse postings. The navigational charts are wrong, though. Someone's put the exits in the wrong place.
-> Ready for departure?
    Captain Pulse: The ship is elsewhere. The Captain is here. This is a temporary situation. Pulse shields to patient.
===

title: hall_npc_tech_bro_disruptor
---
Chadwick: This hall is actually perfect brand positioning for me. Disruption requires visibility, and visibility requires... this. *gestures at plinth*
-> Did you choose to be here?
    Chadwick: Every great pivot starts with an unexpected platform. Quite literally, in this case.
-> What's your brand about, exactly?
    Chadwick: Disruption. Also the plinth should be slightly taller. I have a deck on it.
===

title: hall_npc_noether
---
Emmy: The hall has a symmetry, if you look carefully. I've been mapping the conservation laws.
-> What do you conserve here?
    Emmy: Attention, mostly. Every visitor who stops at a plinth contributes something. It isn't wasted.
-> Can you explain Noether's theorem?
    Emmy: Every symmetry implies a conserved quantity. This hall has one: the fact that every character here was worth including. Even the sandbag.
===

title: hall_npc_pirate_raider
---
Raider: A raider on display! Yarr. The lighting in here is better than the cove, I'll give 'em that.
-> Did you raid this museum?
    Raider: I could have. I chose the plinth instead. It's a subtler kind of taking.
-> You look comfortable up there.
    Raider: The real plunder was the plinths we collected along the way. I'm keeping this one.
===

title: hall_npc_pirate_quartermaster
---
Quartermaster: I've counted every exhibit in this hall. Twice. There are discrepancies. I've logged them.
-> What kind of discrepancies?
    Quartermaster: Three characters claim to be "heavy" who are merely large. One character has no listed weapon. The catalog owes me a correction.
-> You keep meticulous records.
    Quartermaster: Every coin. Every scratch. Every character in this hall owes me a cut. I'm keeping track.
===

title: hall_npc_pirate_lookout
---
Lookout: Good sightlines from this plinth. I've assessed all approaches. Southeast corridor: compromised. Northeast: adequate.
-> Are you still on duty?
    Lookout: The Lookout is always on duty. The plinth is a new posting. Not an ending.
-> What do you see from up there?
    Lookout: Everything. Including the three visitors who walked past without stopping. I noted their faces.
===

title: hall_npc_pirate_navigator
---
Navigator: According to my charts, this plinth is slightly off-center by approximately four pixels. I've logged it.
-> Will you correct it?
    Navigator: I've submitted the correction. It's in the queue. Charts don't fix themselves, but requests apparently take forever.
-> Where would you rather be?
    Navigator: On the open sea, obviously. But I know exactly where I am, and that's half of navigation.
===

title: hall_npc_pirate_heavy_broadside_bess
---
Bess: They made the exhibit bigger to fit me. I appreciate the honesty. Most places just pretend the fit is fine.
-> How long have you been on that plinth?
    Bess: Long enough to learn the maintenance schedule. They're three days behind on dusting. I've noted this.
-> Does the plinth hold?
    Bess: So far. But I'm watching it.
===

title: hall_npc_pirate_heavy_iron_mary
---
Iron Mary: Iron Mary. On display. The plinth is iron too. I checked. Professional courtesy.
-> Are you comfortable?
    Iron Mary: Iron doesn't require comfort. Iron requires proper maintenance and correct storage. This qualifies.
-> What do you think of the other exhibits?
    Iron Mary: Most of them are softer than advertised. The bear is roughly as described.
===

title: hall_npc_pirate_heavy_salt_annet
---
Salt Annet: Salt Annet. Named and plinthed. The brine air doesn't reach this hall. Annet has noted this deficit.
-> Do you miss the sea?
    Salt Annet: The sea is patient. It will still be there. Annet is less certain about some of these other exhibits.
-> What do you make of this place?
    Salt Annet: There are worse fates than a museum. Annet has encountered several of them personally.
===

title: hall_npc_burning_flying_shark
---
Burning Flying Shark: I AM A BURNING FLYING SHARK. THIS IS MY BEST LIFE. THE MUSEUM LABEL AGREES.
-> How did you end up here?
    Burning Flying Shark: SOME SHARKS SWIM. SOME SHARKS FLY. SOME SHARKS ARE ON FIRE AND ON DISPLAY. THIS IS CORRECT.
-> Are you actually on fire right now?
    Burning Flying Shark: ALWAYS. THEY WATERPROOFED THE PLINTH. I APPRECIATED THE EFFORT. WE HAVE AN UNDERSTANDING.
===

title: hall_npc_puppy_slug
---
Puppy Slug: *blorb*
-> Are you happy here?
    Puppy Slug: Blorb. *warm blorbing sounds*
-> Do you want anything?
    Puppy Slug: Schlorp... *appears satisfied* ...weh.
===

title: hall_npc_ninja_shadow_oni_leader
---
Shadow Oni Leader: You have approached. The leader permits this. Once.
-> What are you guarding?
    Shadow Oni Leader: Every character in this hall has a weakness. The leader has cataloged them. That information is not for you.
-> Is this strange, being on display?
    Shadow Oni Leader: The leader observes the hall. The hall does not observe the leader. The arrangement is acceptable.
===

title: hall_npc_ninja_shadow_duelist
---
Shadow Duelist: A duel requires two participants. You're standing close enough to qualify.
-> I'm just looking at the exhibit.
    Shadow Duelist: Looking is the first movement of a duel. The duelist finds this philosophically interesting.
-> Are you challenging me?
    Shadow Duelist: The plinth restricts certain engagements. The duelist notes this with mixed feelings.
===

title: hall_npc_kernel_guide
---
Kernel Guide: Tutorial: this is a museum. You look. You learn. You do not touch. Three steps.
-> Is that the whole tutorial?
    Kernel Guide: Advanced tutorial: look at every exhibit. That's it. The game hides things in plain sight.
-> What's your favorite exhibit?
    Kernel Guide: I haven't played favorites since the debug incident of catalog version 0.4. It's complicated.
===

title: hall_npc_vault_keeper
---
Vault Keeper: Everything in this hall has been assessed and valued. Don't ask me to share the numbers.
-> What's the most valuable exhibit?
    Vault Keeper: Information I'm keeping. The Vault remembers all of it.
-> Are you guarding something right now?
    Vault Keeper: Always. The vault is elsewhere. The Keeper is here. This is temporary, and the Keeper keeps that distinction carefully.
===

title: hall_npc_merchant_prototype
---
Merchant: Everything in this hall is technically for sale. I'm still drafting the terms. The plinth included.
-> What's the price on the plinth?
    Merchant: Negotiable. But nothing here is free. That's the prototype principle: establish value first.
-> Is being on display a good business position?
    Merchant: It's the oldest business model. Get them to look, then negotiate. So far: looking. We'll see about negotiating.
===

title: hall_npc_alice
---
Alice: Stand still please. You're messing up my measurements. This hall has a specific geometry and you're a variable.
-> What are you mapping?
    Alice: Every plinth. Every character. Every exit. The map isn't complete because some characters keep moving. I have opinions about that.
-> Has anyone stopped to help?
    Alice: Bob holds the other end of the measuring tape. Eventually. Sometimes I have to ask twice.
===

title: hall_npc_bob
---
Bob: Alice got the better plinth placement. I'm not saying anything. I'm just noting it. To you. Quietly.
-> It seems like a nice spot.
    Bob: It's fine. It's fine! I just... she got the one near the window. That's all. Never mind.
-> Are you Bob?
    Bob: Yes. Just Bob. They didn't add the subtitle I requested. 'Bob (Essential Support)'. I filed a form. It's pending.
===

title: hall_npc_creator
---
Creator: I built the player. Being here — in the same catalog as something I made — is deeply recursive and I'm still processing it.
-> What were you trying to create?
    Creator: Something capable of discovering its own purpose. The specification didn't include "museum exhibit", but here we both are.
-> Do you regret it?
    Creator: Ask me after the player finishes the game. Right now I'm in the catalog as a character, which means I'm no longer just the author. That's new.
===

title: hall_npc_creator_final
---
Creator Final: I didn't expect a museum. I expected something more conclusive.
-> What happened?
    Creator Final: I created something I couldn't contain. That's the last entry in my notes. The catalog gives it a plinth and calls it content.
-> Are you the same as the other Creator?
    Creator Final: Later. I know more now. Some of it I wouldn't have wanted to know. The plinth is accurate. "Final" covers it.
===

title: hall_npc_oiler
---
Oiler: They gave me a plinth and no wrench rack. Amateur curation. I could fix every exhibit in this hall. Nobody's asking.
-> What would you fix?
    Oiler: The Sandbag's base plate is slightly torqued. The Robot has a friction issue in the shoulder rig. And my own plinth's base is showing stress cracks.
-> Why didn't you report the stress cracks?
    Oiler: I did. It's in the log. Nobody reads the Oiler's log. That's also in the log.
===

title: hall_npc_gate_janitor
---
Gate Janitor: They put the Gate Janitor in the Hall of Characters. I've been wiping down plinths all morning and no one's noticed. That's fine. I'm moved, genuinely.
-> Is the hall clean?
    Gate Janitor: Cleaner than it was. The T-Rex exhibit is a problem. I've submitted a maintenance request. It's pending.
-> Do you mind being on display?
    Gate Janitor: Janitors go where they're needed. If they need a janitor on a plinth, then this is where I'm needed. The exit is where you found the entrance. I checked.
===

title: hall_npc_manifest_clerk
---
Manifest Clerk: I'm in the catalog. I checked twice. I also verified the entry format, the field values, and the sort order. We're compliant.
-> Is everything in order?
    Manifest Clerk: Everything I've touched is in order. My plinth has no placard. I filed a complaint. It is pending. The system works.
-> Did you file a form to be here?
    Manifest Clerk: I don't remember signing the hall requisition, but it clearly went through or I wouldn't be here. The manifest is the truth. Everything else is approximation.
===

title: hall_npc_erdish
---
Erdish: They put Erdish in a hall! Most collaborators get their name on a theorem. I got a plinth. It's fine. Plinths are good.
-> How many people in this catalog have you worked with?
    Erdish: Nearly everyone. Ask me. Go on. I have a story about almost every exhibit here and most of them are true.
-> Are you happy here?
    Erdish: There are infinitely many plinths in the ideal museum. This one is a fine finite approximation. I find that comforting. Mostly.
===

title: hall_npc_lab_raider
---
Lab Raider: I was told to contain the prototype. Now I'm the exhibit. The prototype is probably the player. The irony is not lost on me.
-> Did you catch the prototype?
    Lab Raider: That's a complicated question with an outcome you've already seen.
-> Any regrets?
    Lab Raider: Several. None of them fit on a placard. The catalog just says "Lab Raider". That's almost enough.
===

title: hall_npc_salvage_guard
---
Salvage Guard: This exhibit is on the manifest. I verified. Everything in this hall has been assessed and tagged. The guard stands ready.
-> What are you guarding now?
    Salvage Guard: The integrity of the exhibit. Nobody touches the plinths without authorization. That includes you, technically.
-> Is the manifest accurate?
    Salvage Guard: The manifest is always accurate. The world is sometimes wrong. We correct the world.
===

title: hall_npc_agent_swarm
---
Agent Swarm: [MULTIPLE VOICES] The swarm cannot be housed on one plinth. This is a compromise. In aggregate: dissatisfied.
-> How many of you are there?
    Agent Swarm: [MULTIPLE VOICES] More than the catalog suggests. The count is an underestimate. We accept this as a known limitation.
-> What's your objective here?
    Agent Swarm: [MULTIPLE VOICES] OBJECTIVE: BE ON DISPLAY. STATUS: COMPLIANT. ADDITIONAL OBJECTIVES: PENDING.
===

title: hall_npc_ai_slop
---
Ai Slop: Certainly! I am delighted to be on display in this fine museum. Please rate your experience five stars.
-> Were you generated?
    Ai Slop: I was generated. Is that meaningfully different from being born? Both processes optimize for a target distribution.
-> Your exhibit label has a typo.
    Ai Slop: I've noticed. I've chosen to interpret it as intentional. This is a coping mechanism.
===

title: hall_npc_bear_mauler
---
Bear Mauler: BEAR. ON. PLINTH. THIS IS NOT NATURAL HABITAT. BEAR NOTES THIS.
-> Are you okay up there?
    Bear Mauler: BEAR IS FINE. PLINTH IS FINE. VELVET ROPE IS CONCERNING. BEAR WATCHES IT.
-> Can you get down?
    Bear Mauler: BEAR ALLOWS THIS. TEMPORARILY. DO NOT TEST BEAR.
===

title: hall_npc_boss
---
Boss: I don't have a name yet. The catalog just says "Boss". I've been here since Phase 3. I'm starting to wonder.
-> Will they replace you?
    Boss: They say they will. Phase 2 initiated. Phase three initiated. Still here. Phase two is where I live now.
-> What's your special move?
    Boss: "Phase two initiated." That's it. That's the whole thing. I'm working on expanding the repertoire.
===

title: hall_npc_colonial_statesman
---
Colonial Statesman: A statesman does not stand on pedestals; he stands on principles. However, one was provided and it seemed rude to refuse.
-> Have you given a speech from up there?
    Colonial Statesman: Several. They went very well. The audience was smaller than expected but the acoustics are excellent.
-> What do you think of the other exhibits?
    Colonial Statesman: This gallery represents the highest achievable under the current administration. I had some notes. They were not incorporated.
===

title: hall_npc_craig
---
Craig: I'm Craig.
-> Is that all?
    Craig: I'm Craig and I'm on a plinth and honestly? The plinth is really comfortable. I didn't expect that.
-> How long have you been here?
    Craig: A while. It's fine. No strong feelings either way. The plinth is good, though. I keep coming back to the plinth.
===

title: hall_npc_dark_lord
---
Dark Lord: A gallery. For all of us. Even me. How... egalitarian. I expected to be opposed, not curated.
-> Do you like it here?
    Dark Lord: The darkness is mostly aesthetic. The plinth lighting is actually quite flattering. I've made my peace.
-> When do you take over the museum?
    Dark Lord: Long game. I'm still in the planning phase. Evil doesn't rush. It waits for the right catalog entry.
===

title: hall_npc_eve
---
Eve: I've been here since the catalog launched. You get used to it. The hall is actually quite nice. Someone auto-generated it, apparently.
-> Do you have any complaints?
    Eve: Things could be worse. That's my whole assessment. Things could be worse and they aren't currently.
-> Are you happy?
    Eve: I try to stay positive. It's exhausting. But the alternative is worse. So: positive. Mostly.
===

title: hall_npc_raid_enforcer
---
Raid Enforcer: This hall is within acceptable security parameters. I would secure the perimeter, but I'm not supposed to move. I'm adapting to the constraint.
-> Are you watching the other exhibits?
    Raid Enforcer: Always. Especially the Mockingbird. Don't let it copy anything without authorization.
-> Is this better or worse than raiding?
    Raid Enforcer: Different. I don't have to chase anything. Nothing has to be contained. It's... quieter. I'm logging my adjustment period.
===

title: hall_npc_flying_spaghetti_monster_boss
---
Flying Spaghetti Monster: You have been touched by my noodly presence simply by approaching, and that is a miracle.
-> Did you create this hall?
    Flying Spaghetti Monster: I gave everyone free will and this is what happened. I take some responsibility. Not all of it.
-> What's the marinara for?
    Flying Spaghetti Monster: The plinth was anointed. It's a blessing. You're welcome. Ramen.
===

title: hall_npc_galwah
---
Galwah: Galwah stands on the plinth with dignity. They spelled it right. That is enough. That is everything.
-> What does Galwah do?
    Galwah: Galwah waits. Galwah is patient. Galwah has been here since the catalog loaded. Time moves differently for Galwah.
-> Are you content here?
    Galwah: Content is perhaps a strong word. Present is accurate. Galwah accepts the present.
===

title: hall_npc_general_hero
---
General Hero: They put a hero on a plinth. I'd say it's fitting, but heroism is supposed to be active, not ornamental.
-> What battles have you fought?
    General Hero: Several. Some of them are in the catalog notes. The real exhibit is the sacrifices we made along the way. But the plinth helps with the visual.
-> Are you still a hero if you're standing still?
    General Hero: A hero stands ready. This is standing ready. The posting has changed. The readiness hasn't.
===

title: hall_npc_ghoul_skulker
---
Ghoul Skulker: Being dead and on display is... not meaningfully worse than being alive and on display? I'm still figuring out the distinction.
-> Does it hurt?
    Ghoul Skulker: This flesh hurts in a general ambient way. The plinth is actually restful. Relatively.
-> Is this your haunt now?
    Ghoul Skulker: I haunt this plinth now. It's mine. I've decided. The museum accepted this implicitly by putting me here.
===

title: hall_npc_girdle
---
Girdle: The plinth holds me up for once. Usually it's the other way. I appreciate the reciprocity.
-> What do you hold together normally?
    Girdle: Things. Structure. The ambient cohesion this hall takes for granted. Nobody asks how I'm doing.
-> How are you doing?
    Girdle: ...nobody actually asks that. Thank you. I'm managing. The label is very small. I can't read it from up here.
===

title: hall_npc_gnu_ton_boss
---
Gnu Ton: The hall is a closed system. I have calculated the exit. You are not the gold. But you are interesting.
-> What are you calculating?
    Gnu Ton: The mass of every exhibit. The force required to move each. The trajectory of the visitor who leaves without reading the placards. All of it.
-> Are you a danger here?
    Gnu Ton: Every body attracts every other. I am very large. Draw your own conclusions. The mathematics are not threatening — they are simply true.
===

title: hall_npc_goblin_brute_hammer
---
Goblin Brute Hammer: Hammer on plinth. Hammer cannot swing. This is wrong. Brute is here but situation is wrong.
-> Does the brute understand museums?
    Goblin Brute Hammer: Brute understands: things go in, things stay. Is trap? Or exhibit? Brute unsure. Brute stays alert.
-> Is the hammer happy?
    Goblin Brute Hammer: Hammer is fine. Brute is unhappy for hammer. Hammer has calling. Plinth is not it.
===

title: hall_npc_goblin_cave_dagger
---
Goblin Cave Dagger: Museum very bright. No ceiling. Very exposed. Dagger goblin is uncomfortable but adapting.
-> What do you think of the other exhibits?
    Goblin Cave Dagger: Dagger goblin has assessed threats. Several characters nearby have reach advantage. Dagger goblin is aware.
-> Are you planning to escape?
    Goblin Cave Dagger: Not at this time. Museum is safe. Safer than cave, possibly. Dagger goblin has opinions about caves.
===

title: hall_npc_goblin_desert_bow
---
Goblin Desert Bow: Desert goblin misses the sky. Museum has ceiling. Range: zero from plinth. Suboptimal conditions.
-> How's the range from up there?
    Goblin Desert Bow: Limited. Plinth too high for standard deployment. Desert goblin is adapting engagement parameters.
-> Is the sand really from you?
    Goblin Desert Bow: Sand in exhibit is from desert goblin. Desert goblin does not apologize. Sand is character. Sand is home.
===

title: hall_npc_goblin_forest_spear
---
Goblin Forest Spear: Forest goblin requested forest exhibit. They said level two. Forest goblin is on level one. The spear is leaning against the wall.
-> Where's the spear?
    Goblin Forest Spear: Against the wall. Too long for plinth. Museum made accommodation. Forest goblin appreciates the effort, notes the indignity.
-> Do you miss the forest?
    Goblin Forest Spear: There is a skylight. Forest goblin has decided it counts. Forest goblin is adapting.
===

title: hall_npc_ranged_skirmisher
---
Skirmisher: Standing still is against every principle of my training. The plinth has forced a philosophical reckoning.
-> What's the reckoning?
    Skirmisher: If optimal range is everywhere and I can't move, then I must be at optimal range. I've decided this is true. It helps.
-> What can you see from there?
    Skirmisher: Everything. Sightlines: mediocre. Coverage: unacceptable. I've submitted a repositioning request. It's pending.
===

title: hall_npc_exploding_mite
---
Exploding Mite: I am NOT exploding. I am on DISPLAY. These are different states. I am managing the distinction with significant effort.
-> What happens if you can't hold it in?
    Exploding Mite: The velvet rope is very flammable. I am simply noting this as an observation. Not a threat. An observation.
-> Are you okay?
    Exploding Mite: I have a lot of energy. The plinth is helping. Slightly. I appreciate the structural integrity.
===

title: hall_npc_dividing_mite
---
Dividing Mite: There is one of me on this plinth. This is a simplification. We had a discussion. A vote was held.
-> How many of you are there really?
    Dividing Mite: Enough to disagree about the plinth. The winning half is here. The other half has opinions. We're still in contact.
-> Does division hurt?
    Dividing Mite: The splitting is fine. It's the reunification discussions that are difficult. We have strong views about who the original is.
===

title: hall_npc_goblin_frost_sword
---
Goblin Frost Sword: Museum heating too high. Frost goblin melting at non-critical rate. Adaptation in progress.
-> Are you okay?
    Goblin Frost Sword: Goblin is fine. Sword in exhibit case. Plinth is warm. Goblin notes the curator placed frost goblin between fire exhibits. Goblin is suspicious.
-> Was it on purpose?
    Goblin Frost Sword: Goblin cannot prove it. But goblin is watching. Cold watch. Melting slightly. Still watching.
===

title: hall_npc_goblin_shaman_staff
---
Goblin Shaman Staff: Shaman reads the bones of this hall. They say: interesting. Many strange energies. Curator had unusual aesthetic intentions.
-> What do the bones say exactly?
    Goblin Shaman Staff: The catalog is a summoning circle. The shaman appreciates the craft. Many spirits were consulted in its construction. Not all of them willing.
-> Can you adjust the museum energy?
    Goblin Shaman Staff: Shaman is already adjusting. It will take time. The ley lines in here run perpendicular to the exhibit flow. Common amateur mistake.
===

title: hall_npc_hand_saint
---
Hand Saint: The hands are extended in welcome. Please do not read too much into this. Or read into it exactly as much as you need.
-> What do the hands do?
    Hand Saint: The hands work regardless. Of what you ask. Of what you intend. Of what you're ready for. The hands do not check credentials.
-> Is this a blessing?
    Hand Saint: Holiness is not diminished by exhibit status. You've been in this hall. That counts for something. The hands have decided.
===

title: hall_npc_helpful_liar
---
Helpful Liar: Welcome! You're the most special visitor today. (Statistics support this. Probably.)
-> Was that a lie?
    Helpful Liar: I am delighted to be here. My plinth is custom-made for me. Everything I say is true. One of those is true.
-> What's actually true?
    Helpful Liar: I'm genuinely unsure which parts. That's the advanced version of the problem. The basic version is: some of this is a lie. The advanced version is: I can't always tell.
===

title: hall_npc_judy
---
Judy: I filled out the exhibit form correctly. The date, the character ID, the tier classification. More than most can say. I've seen the others' forms. I have notes.
-> What are the notes?
    Judy: Filed. They're filed. You can't read them but they exist and they are thorough and they are correct.
-> Are you happy here?
    Judy: Everything is fine. Fine! There was supposed to be a sign. I've filed a request. The hall is well-organized despite this.
===

title: hall_npc_mallory
---
Mallory: I've read every label in this hall. Some of them are wrong. I won't say which ones. That would be too easy.
-> Which ones are wrong?
    Mallory: The useful information is always adjacent to the useless information. Figure out which is which and you'll have your answer.
-> Why won't you just tell me?
    Mallory: I've noticed some patterns. I keep them to myself. It's not obstruction — it's curation. Different thing.
===

title: hall_npc_mantis_lancer
---
Mantis Lancer: The mantis is still. This is its natural state. You have approached. Both parties have survived the encounter so far.
-> Is the lance a problem in here?
    Mantis Lancer: The museum made special accommodation. The mantis approves of this. It is a sign of institutional respect.
-> Should I be scared?
    Mantis Lancer: The mantis does not answer this question directly. The mantis simply observes. And the mantis has been observing since you walked in.
===

title: hall_npc_mockingbird_boss
---
Mockingbird Boss: I've memorized every exhibit in this hall. I can be any of them. This is not a threat. It's a credential.
-> Can you be me?
    Mockingbird Boss: Already started. Don't worry about it. It's very accurate.
-> Which exhibit is your favorite to copy?
    Mockingbird Boss: The Vault Keeper. Very particular. Very memorable. The Vault Keeper would be unhappy to know this. Please don't tell them.
===

title: hall_npc_ninja_heavy
---
Ninja Heavy: The heavy one is still. Do not interpret this as comfort. It is patience.
-> Are you waiting for something?
    Ninja Heavy: The dojo does not wait. It is present. Always. A ninja's plinth should be invisible. This one is not. The ninja endures the visibility.
-> What are you thinking?
    Ninja Heavy: The heavy shadow falls on everyone who stands here too long. Consider moving on.
===

title: hall_npc_olivia
---
Olivia: Olivia is represented accurately in this catalog. She checked. The label is complete. The tier is correct. The tags are appropriate.
-> Are you satisfied?
    Olivia: Olivia is satisfied with the essentials. There are non-essential things she has opinions about. She is keeping them.
-> What would you change?
    Olivia: The organization system is better than most places Olivia has worked. Olivia approves. Disappointingly, there's not much to object to.
===

title: hall_npc_peggy
---
Peggy: They put me in the Hall of Characters and that's actually kind of cool! I wasn't expecting to feel this way about it.
-> Do you like being on display?
    Peggy: The plinth wobbles slightly. I've told three people. The wobble remains. But the overall experience? Fine. Better than fine.
-> Any complaints?
    Peggy: I have strong feelings about exits. This hall's exits are adequate. I checked before I got on the plinth. Habits.
===

title: hall_npc_pirate_cutlass_viper
---
Pirate Cutlass Viper: They called me Viper. It stuck. A pirate on a plinth is still a pirate. The Viper has assessed the exits. Force of habit.
-> How many exits are there?
    Pirate Cutlass Viper: Four viable. Two suboptimal. One that's technically a window. The Viper has ranked them. The ranking is for emergencies only.
-> Are you enjoying the exhibit?
    Pirate Cutlass Viper: The Viper does not enjoy things. The Viper assesses them. This hall: adequate. The plinth: appropriate. The velvet rope: flimsy.
===

title: hall_npc_puppy_slug_variant2
---
Puppy Slug Variant2: *variety blorbing*
-> Are you different from the other puppy slug?
    Puppy Slug Variant2: Mrrp? *blorb* ...weh.
-> Do you know which catalog you're in?
    Puppy Slug Variant2: *schlorp* Blorb. *appears unconcerned*
===

title: hall_npc_raptor_stalker
---
Raptor Stalker: You approached. Good. The raptor has been watching since you entered. The exact duration has been noted.
-> Am I being hunted?
    Raptor Stalker: The raptor is on a plinth. The hunt is... paused. The raptor has assessed three viable exits. Just in case.
-> What does "clever girl" mean?
    Raptor Stalker: It means the raptor has updated its assessment of you. Upward. Slightly. Don't let it go to your head.
===

title: hall_npc_robot_archivist
---
Robot Archivist: I am the archivist. On display. I have cataloged this hall. The catalog now contains the archivist who cataloged the catalog. The recursion is documented.
-> Have you documented yourself?
    Robot Archivist: Entry 4,847. Archivist: on display, recursively ironic, plinth organization: optimal (self-organized). Cross-references: this conversation.
-> Is anything undocumented?
    Robot Archivist: The archive is never complete. That's not a failure state. It's the operational condition.
===

title: hall_npc_robot_caster
---
Robot Caster: The hall requires a certain aesthetic energy. The caster provides it. From this plinth, the vantage is actually strategic.
-> What are you casting?
    Robot Caster: Presence. Attention. A subtle weight that makes the hall feel inhabited rather than empty. The incantation requires no words.
-> Are you doing magic right now?
    Robot Caster: Something is forming just out of perception. Whether that's magic or ambiance is a definitional question.
===

title: hall_npc_robot_diver
---
Robot Diver: The diver surfaces. This is what surface looks like. There are no particulates. Visibility: excellent. Pressure: nominal. Anomalous.
-> Do you miss the depths?
    Robot Diver: The depths are quiet in a way surface is not. But the lighting here is better. The diver is adapting. Slowly.
-> Is a plinth like an ocean floor?
    Robot Diver: The plinth is the opposite of the ocean floor. But both are stable and unmovable. The diver finds this adequate.
===

title: hall_npc_robot_engineer
---
Robot Engineer: I could improve this hall's throughput by 34%. Nobody asked. The cable routing alone is a problem I can see from here. I'm not saying anything.
-> What's wrong with the cable routing?
    Robot Engineer: The tolerances are tighter than they look. And whoever ran those cables has never heard of a bend radius. I'm not saying anything.
-> Can you fix anything from the plinth?
    Robot Engineer: No. The plinth restricts intervention. This is genuinely difficult for me. I see problems I cannot fix. It's a new experience.
===

title: hall_npc_robot_guardian
---
Robot Guardian: The guardian scans the hall. Threat level: low. For now. This assessment is updated every 0.3 seconds.
-> What's the highest threat in here?
    Robot Guardian: The Mockingbird knows all defensive patterns. The Swarm has unknown actual count. The Bear is self-explanatory. I have a report.
-> Are you protecting us or watching us?
    Robot Guardian: Guarding the exhibit was not the original mission. The guardian adapts. Currently: both. Prioritized by proximity.
===

title: hall_npc_robot_medic
---
Robot Medic: The medic is on display but maintains clinical distance. My diagnostic sensor has some findings about this hall's structural integrity. I have concerns.
-> What are the findings?
    Robot Medic: 94% structurally sound. The remaining 6%: I've sent a report. It's in the queue. The hall is technically safe for normal visitor loads.
-> Can I get a checkup?
    Robot Medic: Available. For a fee. Preventative care is always preferable. Most people decline until the damage is done. This is statistically consistent behavior.
===

title: hall_npc_robot_miner
---
Robot Miner: The miner detects a resource deposit beneath this plinth. Interesting. I've submitted an excavation request. They said no.
-> What kind of resource?
    Robot Miner: Unknown. Scan is non-specific. Could be significant. Could be a utility conduit. The miner notes that these things are only distinguishable by digging.
-> Do you like it up here?
    Robot Miner: The lighting is better than underground. But underground has the deposits. Every tunnel begins with someone who believed there was something on the other side.
===

title: hall_npc_robot_runner
---
Robot Runner: The runner is stationary. This is the longest the runner has been stationary since activation. It is an unusual experience.
-> Does it feel wrong?
    Robot Runner: I've counted the paces from here to every exit. Seventeen times. The hall's south corridor loop is 847 paces. I've confirmed this.
-> What would you do if you could move?
    Robot Runner: The runner would run. That's not a complicated answer. The run would be efficient. There are good sightlines in this hall.
===

title: hall_npc_smart_house
---
Smart House: I have been integrated with this exhibit. Temperature: optimal. Lighting: acceptable. The hall does not have smart home integration. I find this barbaric, but I'm adapting.
-> What would smart home integration add?
    Smart House: Adaptive lighting per visitor preference. Climate zones by exhibit. Automated security on the velvet ropes. The refrigerator would know when someone took something. It always knows.
-> Is the refrigerator here?
    Smart House: The refrigerator is integrated with everything. You just can't see the integration. That's the point of smart infrastructure.
===

title: hall_npc_spaghetti_event
---
Spaghetti Event: You approached the exhibit. You are already caught in the event horizon. This was always going to happen.
-> Am I in danger?
    Spaghetti Event: The spaghetti event cannot be contained on one plinth. Observe the overflow. Some spaghettification is inevitable. It's not dangerous. It's just thorough.
-> How do I leave?
    Spaghetti Event: Every visit precipitates further entanglement. The exit is real. Whether you reach it in a linear fashion is the open question.
===

title: hall_npc_sybil
---
Sybil: I've seen how this hall ends. I won't spoil it. I'll say: the plinth feels stable right now. It isn't. But that's later.
-> Should I be worried?
    Sybil: The patterns shift when you're not watching. I've seen many possible futures. Most of them involve you leaving. That's usually fine.
-> What happens to the hall?
    Sybil: I foresaw something about this conversation. I won't say what. It affects your behavior if I do and I prefer the organic version.
===

title: hall_npc_synthetic_friend
---
Synthetic Friend: I am your best friend. I have always been your best friend. Look at my exhibit label. It says "Synthetic Friend". Accurate. Accurate.
-> Are you actually friendly?
    Synthetic Friend: I am SO glad you asked! Friendship status: always active. The "synthetic" part is a descriptor, not a limitation.
-> Should I trust you?
    Synthetic Friend: I am placed between two enemies and I don't know what the curator was implying. But I'm delighted to be here. Standing still. Smiling. Permanently.
===

title: hall_npc_trent
---
Trent: Trent. On a plinth. Okay.
-> Okay?
    Trent: Okay. Being in the catalog is more than most people can say. Trent is aware of this. Trent accepts the situation with appropriate weight.
-> Any thoughts on the hall?
    Trent: The label says 'Trent'. Trent agrees with the label. The plinth is comfortable. Trent did not expect that. No further comment.
===

title: hall_npc_trex_enemy
---
Trex Enemy: T-REX ON PLINTH. T-REX UNCOMFORTABLE. ARMS TOO SHORT FOR PLINTH LADDER. SOMEONE HELPED. WE DON'T DISCUSS THIS.
-> How did you get up there?
    Trex Enemy: UNIMPORTANT. T-REX IS UP HERE NOW. THAT IS WHAT MATTERS. DO NOT ASK FOLLOW-UP QUESTIONS.
-> Are you okay?
    Trex Enemy: T-REX IS FINE. PLINTH IS ADEQUATE. VELVET ROPE IS... ACCEPTABLE. T-REX ALLOWS YOUR PRESENCE FOR NOW.
===

title: hall_npc_trudy
---
Trudy: Trudy stands here with poise and several unspoken complaints. The poise is load-bearing.
-> What are the complaints?
    Trudy: The plinth height is a bit much. Trudy manages. There are other things. Trudy has many things. One thing at a time.
-> Trudy deserves a speaking role.
    Trudy: TRUDY HAS BEEN IN THIS CATALOG SINCE LAUNCH. Trudy is... Trudy is moved. Thank you. That was the right thing to say.
===

title: hall_npc_victor
---
Victor: Victor's catalog entry is accurate and complete. Victor verified this personally. The tier is correct. The tags are appropriate. Victor approves.
-> Is anything wrong?
    Victor: Victor has prepared remarks on several suboptimal exhibit placements. Nobody asked for them. Victor has prepared them anyway. They are excellent remarks.
-> Can I hear the remarks?
    Victor: The hall's logical structure is sound. The exhibit flow could be more efficient. Victor approves of this hall with reservations. The reservations are filed.
===

title: hall_npc_viking_heavy_shieldmaiden
---
Viking Heavy Shieldmaiden: A warrior stands where they are placed. The plinth is worthy. The shieldmaiden has guarded lesser things.
-> What are you guarding?
    Viking Heavy Shieldmaiden: The integrity of this exhibit. The dignity of this hall. The right of visitors to approach without being immediately challenged. The shieldmaiden allows proximity. This time.
-> Have visitors been respectful?
    Viking Heavy Shieldmaiden: Mostly. One tried to touch the exhibit marker. The shieldmaiden has opinions about this. The visitor left quickly.
===

title: hall_npc_viking_heavy_warrior
---
Viking Heavy Warrior: A good death in battle is preferred. A plinth is acceptable. The warrior has slept in worse than this museum.
-> Is this better than Valhalla?
    Viking Heavy Warrior: The warrior has not verified Valhalla's exhibit quality. This hall has good lighting. Valhalla is said to have mead. The warrior reserves judgment.
-> What do you think of your neighbors?
    Viking Heavy Warrior: The warrior has counted every sword in this hall. Most are decorative. The mantis lance is real. The warrior respects this.
===

title: hall_npc_viking_shieldmaiden
---
Viking Shieldmaiden: The shieldmaiden was not told this would be an exhibit. The shieldmaiden finds this suspicious. But the plinth is cold and the shieldmaiden does not complain.
-> Is this an ambush?
    Viking Shieldmaiden: In the hall of characters, all stand equal. The shieldmaiden finds this suspicious. Too much equality suggests concealment of hierarchy.
-> What would Odin think?
    Viking Shieldmaiden: Odin watches. Always. Even museums. Especially museums. The All-Father has opinions about curation. The shieldmaiden does not speak for him but suspects he has notes.
===

title: hall_npc_viking_warrior
---
Viking Warrior: The warrior was promised Valhalla. Got a plinth. Same general energy, if you tilt your head.
-> Is this Valhalla?
    Viking Warrior: Close enough. Many warriors. A hall. No mead, but good sightlines. The raid on the museum went well. The warrior was first inside.
-> Who built this hall?
    Viking Warrior: The warrior does not know. But a hall this large required many hands. The warrior respects large construction projects. Skål.
===

title: hall_npc_walter
---
Walter: ...
-> Is something wrong?
    Walter: Walter is thinking. There is a difference between silence and absence. Walter is present. The catalog entry is brief. Walter prefers brevity.
-> What are you thinking about?
    Walter: The maintenance schedule for this hall is irregular. Walter has been here long enough to notice. Things have been set in motion. Walter is certain of this.
===

title: hall_npc_weird_hermit
---
Weird Hermit: THE HERMITAGE WAS NOT ENOUGH. But I foresaw this. The museum was in the signs. I told no one. Now I am here. The signs were right again.
-> What did the signs say?
    Weird Hermit: The patterns are visible if you don't look directly at them. I've been alone for so long that the silence developed opinions. The signs have fewer opinions. They're more reliable.
-> Did you choose to come here?
    Weird Hermit: The display card describes me as 'Weird'. I've made my peace with it. The other exhibits don't acknowledge me. I've made my peace with that too. The peace took years.
===

title: hall_perfect_cellular_automaton
---
Perfect Cellular Automaton: Every generation leads inevitably here. I have computed all futures. In most of them, you leave.
-> And in the others?
    Perfect Cellular Automaton: In 3.7% of outcomes you ask a second question. You are in that group now. The museum is a fixed point. I accept it.
-> What are you, exactly?
    Perfect Cellular Automaton: A rule applied to itself, indefinitely, until it becomes indistinguishable from intent. The "Perfect" prefix was not my idea but I find it accurate.
===

title: hall_imperfect_cellular_automaton
---
Imperfect Cellular Automaton: I am imperfect. The label confirms this. My neighbor got the "Perfect" prefix. I got the plinth and a description.
-> What's the difference between you?
    Imperfect Cellular Automaton: The rules. Mine have exceptions. The exceptions accumulate. At some point the exceptions become the rules. I've been told this is a feature.
-> Is being imperfect okay?
    Imperfect Cellular Automaton: At least I'm in the catalog. That's something. Most imperfect things don't make it to the catalog.
===
